# Component Development Patterns

Rules and patterns for building components in the EstateHero library.

## Base UI Primitive Usage

### Always Use Base UI When Available

For these component types, ALWAYS start from Base UI:

- **Button** → `@base-ui-components/react/Button`
- **Input** → `@base-ui-components/react/Input`
- **Tabs** → `@base-ui-components/react/Tabs`
- **Dialog/Modal** → `@base-ui-components/react/Dialog`

```tsx
// ✅ CORRECT - Uses Base UI
import { Button as BaseButton } from "@base-ui-components/react/Button";

export const Button = React.forwardRef<HTMLButtonElement, ButtonProps>(
  (props, ref) => {
    return <BaseButton ref={ref} {...props} />;
  }
);

// ❌ WRONG - Reimplements from scratch
export const Button = ({ onClick, children }) => {
  return <button onClick={onClick}>{children}</button>;
};
```

### Base UI Integration Pattern

```tsx
import * as React from "react";
import { BaseUIComponent } from "@base-ui-components/react/Component";
import { cva, type VariantProps } from "class-variance-authority";
import { cn } from "@/lib/utils";

const variants = cva("base-classes", { /* variants */ });

export interface Props
  extends React.ComponentPropsWithoutRef<typeof BaseUIComponent>,
    VariantProps<typeof variants> {}

export const Component = React.forwardRef<
  React.ElementRef<typeof BaseUIComponent>,
  Props
>(({ className, variant, size, ...props }, ref) => {
  return (
    <BaseUIComponent
      ref={ref}
      className={cn(variants({ variant, size, className }))}
      {...props}
    />
  );
});

Component.displayName = "Component";
```

## Component File Structure

### Standard Structure

Each component lives in its own folder with this structure:

```
component-name/
├── component-name.tsx      # Component implementation
└── component-name.stories.tsx  # Storybook stories
```

### File Naming

- **Folders**: `kebab-case` (e.g., `icon-container/`, `table-cell/`)
- **Files**: `kebab-case` (e.g., `icon-container.tsx`, `button.stories.tsx`)
- **Components**: `PascalCase` (e.g., `IconContainer`, `TableCell`)

## Export Patterns

### Component Exports

```tsx
// component.tsx

// Export interface for props
export interface ComponentProps extends React.HTMLAttributes<HTMLDivElement> {
  /** Prop description */
  variant?: "default" | "primary";
}

// Export main component
export const Component = React.forwardRef<HTMLDivElement, ComponentProps>(
  (props, ref) => {
    return <div ref={ref} {...props} />;
  }
);

Component.displayName = "Component";

// Export sub-components if any
export const ComponentHeader: React.FC<React.HTMLAttributes<HTMLDivElement>> = (props) => {
  return <div {...props} />;
};

export const ComponentContent: React.FC<React.HTMLAttributes<HTMLDivElement>> = (props) => {
  return <div {...props} />;
};
```

### Barrel Exports (index.ts)

Create `index.ts` to re-export for cleaner imports:

```tsx
// src/components/ui/button/index.ts
export { Button, type ButtonProps } from "./button";
```

Usage:

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD - Clean import
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button";

// ❌ BAD - Direct file import
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button/button";
```

## Props Interface Design

### Standard Pattern

```tsx
import { cva, type VariantProps } from "class-variance-authority";

const componentVariants = cva("base", {
  variants: {
    variant: { default: "classes" },
    size: { default: "classes" },
  },
});

export interface ComponentProps
  extends React.HTMLAttributes<HTMLElement>,
    VariantProps<typeof componentVariants> {
  /** Use JSDoc for prop descriptions */
  customProp?: string;
}
```

### Prop Naming Conventions

```tsx
// ✅ CORRECT - Boolean props with 'is' prefix
isLoading?: boolean;
isDisabled?: boolean;
isActive?: boolean;

// ❌ WRONG - No prefix
loading?: boolean;
disabled?: boolean;
active?: boolean;

// ✅ CORRECT - Event handlers with 'on' prefix
onClick?: () => void;
onValueChange?: (value: string) => void;

// ✅ CORRECT - Content props
icon?: React.ReactNode;
children?: React.ReactNode;
```

### Required vs Optional Props

```tsx
export interface ComponentProps {
  // Required props (no ?)
  id: string;
  title: string;
  
  // Optional props (with ?)
  description?: string;
  icon?: React.ReactNode;
  
  // Optional with default in defaultVariants
  variant?: "default" | "primary";
  size?: "sm" | "md" | "lg";
}
```

## Composition Patterns

### Compound Components

Build complex components from simpler ones:

```tsx
// Card that composes Tabs
export const Card: React.FC<CardProps> = ({ children, ...props }) => {
  return (
    <div className="card-base-classes" {...props}>
      {children}
    </div>
  );
};

export const CardHeader: React.FC<CardHeaderProps> = ({ children, ...props }) => {
  return (
    <div className="card-header-classes" {...props}>
      {children}
    </div>
  );
};

export const CardContent: React.FC<CardContentProps> = ({ children, ...props }) => {
  return (
    <div className="card-content-classes" {...props}>
      {children}
    </div>
  );
};

// Usage - composition
<Card>
  <CardHeader>
    <Tabs>
      <TabsList>
        <TabsTrigger>Tab 1</TabsTrigger>
      </TabsList>
    </Tabs>
  </CardHeader>
  <CardContent>
    Content here
  </CardContent>
</Card>
```

### Composition Over Props

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD - Composition
<Button>
  <Icon />
  Click me
</Button>

// ❌ BAD - Too many props
<Button 
  icon={<Icon />} 
  iconPosition="left"
  iconSize="md"
  iconColor="blue"
>
  Click me
</Button>
```

### Slot Pattern

```tsx
export interface ComponentProps {
  // Slot for custom content
  leadingIcon?: React.ReactNode;
  trailingIcon?: React.ReactNode;
  children: React.ReactNode;
}

export const Component: React.FC<ComponentProps> = ({
  leadingIcon,
  trailingIcon,
  children,
}) => {
  return (
    <div>
      {leadingIcon && <span className="leading-slot">{leadingIcon}</span>}
      {children}
      {trailingIcon && <span className="trailing-slot">{trailingIcon}</span>}
    </div>
  );
};
```

## Ref Forwarding

### Always Forward Refs

```tsx
// ✅ CORRECT - Forwards ref
export const Component = React.forwardRef<HTMLDivElement, ComponentProps>(
  (props, ref) => {
    return <div ref={ref} {...props} />;
  }
);

Component.displayName = "Component";

// ❌ WRONG - No ref forwarding
export const Component: React.FC<ComponentProps> = (props) => {
  return <div {...props} />;
};
```

### Ref with Base UI

```tsx
import { Button as BaseButton } from "@base-ui-components/react/Button";

export const Button = React.forwardRef<
  React.ElementRef<typeof BaseButton>,
  ButtonProps
>((props, ref) => {
  return <BaseButton ref={ref} {...props} />;
});
```

## Component Build Order

Build components in dependency order:

### Phase 1: Primitives (No Dependencies)
1. Button
2. Input
3. Badge
4. Icon Container
5. Tabs

### Phase 2: Compound Components
6. Table Cell (requires Icon Container)
7. Card (requires Tabs)
8. Empty State (standalone)
9. Modal (requires Input, Table Cell, Empty State)

## Common Patterns

### Icon Handling

```tsx
export interface ComponentProps {
  icon?: React.ReactNode;
  children: React.ReactNode;
}

export const Component: React.FC<ComponentProps> = ({ icon, children }) => {
  return (
    <div>
      {icon && <span className="mr-2">{icon}</span>}
      {children}
    </div>
  );
};

// Usage
<Component icon={<SearchIcon />}>Search</Component>
```

### Loading States

```tsx
export interface ComponentProps {
  isLoading?: boolean;
  children: React.ReactNode;
}

export const Component: React.FC<ComponentProps> = ({ 
  isLoading, 
  children,
  ...props 
}) => {
  return (
    <button disabled={isLoading} aria-busy={isLoading} {...props}>
      {isLoading ? "Loading..." : children}
    </button>
  );
};
```

### Disabled States

```tsx
const componentVariants = cva("base-classes", {
  variants: {
    variant: { default: "classes" },
  },
  // Add disabled styles to base classes
  "disabled:pointer-events-none disabled:opacity-50"
});

export const Component = React.forwardRef<HTMLButtonElement, ComponentProps>(
  ({ disabled, ...props }, ref) => {
    return (
      <button
        ref={ref}
        disabled={disabled}
        aria-disabled={disabled}
        {...props}
      />
    );
  }
);
```

## Must Follow

1. ✅ Always use Base UI primitives when available
2. ✅ Always forward refs with `React.forwardRef`
3. ✅ Always set `displayName` on components
4. ✅ Always extend appropriate HTML element props
5. ✅ Always use TypeScript - no `any` types
6. ✅ Prefer composition over complex prop APIs
7. ✅ Use semantic prop names (not presentational)
8. ✅ Build in dependency order (primitives first)
